comments: Smart (BOS) establishes himself in a legal screening position in the path of Finney-Smith (DAL) and he brings his arms out slightly as he turns to roll. The contact to Finney-Smith is marginal and does not impact the defensive play.

Doncic (DAL) gets his right hand to the ball and gathers control over the loose ball. Prior gaining control, Doncic makes some marginal contact with the right arm of Brown (BOS) but the arm contact does not impact the loose ball opportunity.
Brown (BOS) tries to move back in front of Doncic (DAL) and body contact occurs that impacts the latter's SQBR.
Finney-Smith (DAL) establishes himself in a legal screening position in the path of Brown (BOS) and absorbs the marginal contact during the screen.
Williams III (BOS) legally contests the perimeter jump shot from Doncic (DAL).
Kleber (DAL) jumps vertically and then brings his right arm down and onto the ball to deflect Brown's (BOS) driving shot attempt.
Brown (BOS) places a hand on the waist of Dinwiddie (DAL) but the marginal contact has no impact to Dinwiddie's FOM.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Doncic (DAL) passes the ball out of bounds.
Dinwiddie (DAL) briefly brings his arms to the sides of Tatum (BOS) during the post up but the contact is marginal and does not impact Tatum's FOM.
Williams III (BOS) briefly places his hand on Doncic's (DAL) back but the marginal touch does not impact his static position with the ball.
Doncic (DAL) changes directions and extends his off-arm outwards during the drive and some marginal contact occurs with the arm of Brown (BOS) but there is no affect on the defensive play.
Horford (BOS) legally contests Dinwiddie's (DAL) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.

Replay review of the shooting foul called on Doncic (DAL) pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed successful. Doncic makes incidental, 'high-five' contact with the hand of Smart (BOS) after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Dinwiddie (DAL) and Tatum (BOS) engage and disengage during the inbounds play.
Dinwiddie (DAL) makes marginal contact with Tatum's (BOS) side before the start of his upward shooting motion and the contact does not affect his jump shot attempt.
